        <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-text-primary max-w-2xl leading-tight">Three beliefs that shape every engagement.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div class="fade-in border border-border p-8 hover:border-gold transition-colors duration-300">
          <div class="w-8 h-0.5 bg-gold mb-8"></div>
          <p class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-text-primary leading-snug mb-4">Leadership is not a position. It is a pattern of behaviour under pressure.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed">The real test of leadership isn't the good days. It's who you are when the system is failing, the stakeholders are nervous, and the path forward is unclear.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="fade-in border border-border p-8 hover:border-gold transition-colors duration-300">
          <div class="w-8 h-0.5 bg-gold mb-8"></div>
          <p class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-text-primary leading-snug mb-4">Culture is not built in townhalls. It is built in everyday decisions and micro-actions.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed">What leaders do in the ordinary moments — how they respond to failure, how they credit others, how they hold hard conversations — that is the culture.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="fade-in border border-border p-8 hover:border-gold transition-colors duration-300">
          <div class="w-8 h-0.5 bg-gold mb-8"></div>
          <p class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-text-primary leading-snug mb-4">Transformation begins with clarity — not action.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed">The leaders who are stuck aren't short of drive. They're short of clarity about where that drive should go. Get the clarity right and the action becomes obvious.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

